finalise() - Method in class com.doa.engine.DoaObject
Deprecated.
Since DoaEngine v1.1 it is ill-advised to use this method. This method only exists for backwards compatibility. Use DoaHandler.instantiateDoaObject(Class, Object...) for instantiating objects instead.

Finalises this DoaObject's instantiation by adding it to DoaHandler. This method should only be called once, STRICTLY after ALL constructor related tasks are finished. Otherwise, DoaEngine might run into a NullPointerException.

FRONT - Static variable in class com.doa.engine.DoaObject
DoaObjects with a zOrder of DoaObject.FRONT will be drawn in front of all other DoaObjects except DoaObjects with a zOrder of DoaObject.STATIC_FRONT.
